parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor stops working
the seat belt will not retract
the seat belt becomes stuck in the track
the seat belt slows down or hesitates
the seat belt breaks or fails occasionally.

symptoms: Engine check light comes on and won't go off

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, decreased performance, and potentially causing a fire.
Failure of the exhaust system can cause decreased engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to a fire.
A vehicle fire can cause serious injury or death, as well as property damage.
Failure to perform recall repairs can lead to continued safety risks and decreased vehicle performance.
symptoms: Dealership refused to perform recall repairs

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the key to get stuck in the ignition, leading to engine fires, and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: key getting stuck in the ignition
starter burning out or catching fire

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter motor can cause it to burn out or catch fire, leading to engine fires and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
The failure of the alternator can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to engine fires and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
The failure of the battery can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to engine fires and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
The failure of the ignition coil can cause engine misfires, leading to decreased vehicle performance and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In extreme cases, it can also cause fluid leaks, leading to fires.
Transmission slipping can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
A loose speedometer cable can cause the speedometer to fail, leading to inaccurate speed readings and potentially causing accidents.
A transmission coolant line leak can cause fluid to spray onto the exhaust system, leading to fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor transmission servicing can lead to transmission failure, causing the vehicle to lose power and potentially leading to accidents.
